title: Goblet, ca. 1810–25
provenance: M.H. Impey, 172 Walton St. London, SW 3, (8-8-69) purchased by WPW.
description: Inverted pear-shaped bowl with flat bottom, shor stem with ring knop. Plain circular foot. Engraved band with sketchy, scalloped edges contains 4 sprigs inscribed in semicircular areas. Between them are abstract, dotted flowers.

tombstone.epitaph:
Goblet, ca. 1810–25.
ca. 1810–25. glass. Bequest of Walter Phelps Warren. 1986-61-209.
